Don't start paraphrasing Socrates just because you're blind. <P>While I agree with you that American media is full of nausiating ideologies, the Middle East situation is actually UNDERMINED by it. I have family in Israel, and I hear about their first-hand experiences all the time. Imagine your favorite cafe blown up few hours after you've left it, or looking closely at every new person boarding the bus not knowing whether he has a bomb under his coat, and maybe you'll finally realize a fraction of what they have to live with everyday. <P>Yes, there's two sides to every story, but in this case, it's very fucking clear which side is the wrong one.<P>--------------------<P>Voron the Wanderer - <A HREF="http://www.drow.org/eq/roster/viewprofile.php?name=Voron" TARGET=_blank> profile </A><BR>Hierophant -- Blood of the Spider<BR>"Not all those who wander are lost" - J.R.R. Tolkien
