(Not my thesis, I have midterms as well as this project but the ideas intertwine)<P><BR>It's hard not to blast people in threads like this.<P>Oh, you want a solution? Where is YOURS?<P>All I have heard is we need intervention from the international community.  Oh?  How?  Is saying "the international community needs to get involved" an answer (I repeat).  Who?  The US?  The UN? How?  What about sovereignty?  Military action?  Against who?  What about civilians and innocents? What about individual rights - human rights?  Who will offer troops?  <P>You speak of history but do you really know it?  I laugh at the use of history in this thread thus far as it doesn't extend beyond news CLIPS from rightist editorials.  <P>I feel a deep pain for the families of those dieing, but both the ISRAELIES and the PALESTINIANS are taking losses and being hurt in the long run.  <P>   To conclude, I will NOT offer a solution but establish my understanding of the situation.  I am not smart enough to come up with a solution to a problem as deeply rooted in hate as greed, love (yes love), ignorance, propaganda, oil etc.<BR> Don't give me this crap about "we've offered a solution and you just mock us".  The real solution which is subtely agreed to across most of the posts made thus far is that the Palestinians and Arabs should be killed or destroyed.  WOW GREAT SOLUTION - YOU SHOULD JOIN THE SECURITY COUNCIL!<p>[ April 26, 2002: Message edited by: Xyrloc ]<P>--------------------<P>C'mon Shammy Pants!
