<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Shushi wrote, "Judaism is not the religion of Israel, Zionism is."<P>Zionism - The Jewish movement to create a Jewish state.<P>The Jews are the most universally hated and persecuted ethnic group in history.  Theodore Herzl, the founder of the Zionist movement, believed that the hatred of Jews was a direct consequence of thier stateless condition (note: this was long before even the Holocaust).  Herzl and the Zionist founders believed that if the Jews had a nation of thier own, this fact would normalize thier condition in the community of nations.  Jews had been without a state since the "diaspora" of 70AD when the Romans expelled them from the land and it wasn't until the "Palestine Mandate" in 1921 that they once again had a home.  Jewish Zionist were given a small portion of land west of the Jordan as the result in the Allied defeat of the Turks in WWI and eventually used this land to create Israel.  So no... Zionism is not the "religion" of Israel.<P>In addition:<BR>Arab leaders reject the very idea of peace with Israel because without the "Jewish problem" the suffering of the people they rule is all of a sudden seen for what it is, an internal leadership problem rather than a direct product of Israel.  The problem with this situation is that the United States by and large has to work around the present leadership in the Middle East because of the displacement of power.  In many cases Arab leaders are considered "moderate" by Middle East standards.  If the Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia were to step down and free elections were held, Bin Laden would, most likely, be elected.  And these are our BEST allies in the entire Middle East!
</FONT>
