Helcite I don't even know where to begin with what you have said.<P>But i'll at least post one reply to your comments until I can figure out where to even begin.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR> And I'll remind you, go read Sssorn's post. It warrants a discussion about RESOLUTION, that means THE END PRODUCT, not motivation for choosing that end product. If you want to discuss motivation then at least make your discussion pertinent by proposing a viable resolution. Otherwise you'll continue to be met with people that could care less WTF you're posting. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>How are they AT ALL separate? (resolution and motivation).  Seeking a resolution because you (not you, but you in the generic sense) are a humanitarian and love people and seeking a resolution because you hate Arabs or Israelis will dramatically alter the way in which you go about creating/making the resolution happen.<P><BR>I'd also like to note that while that website does ignore many issues dealing with Israelies suffering, it is accurate in MANY of it's articles - articles that are compilations of works from reputable sources and not ramblings of individuals with no credentials.<P>Grim - maybe upon reading some articles on Sharon and TORTURE or his own personal hatreds you might see that his "motivations" (whoops I shouldn't speak of motivation right?) aren't pure as well.  No, Arafat is not clean, no Sharon is not clean, no the US and international community are not clean.  Fundamentalists from the Arab nation are committing atrocities - yes.  Hate filled Israeli police and civilians are as well.  At least acknowledge that it is reciprical otherwise you're not living in the real world. <P>This isn't a problem so easily solved by the US (AS IT HAS SO MANY TIMES) playing daddy (as Ssorn suggests) plotting land it feels appropriate (without any of it's own motivations in mind right?) and then sending men in to spank any naughty children that might not like it.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR> I don't support the idea of "eye for an eye"; that only leads to loss of another eye. If someone took your eye, kill them, cause that's the only way you can save your remaining eye. And Arafat has taken enough eyes to be killed countless times over. So have his people. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Wow.  Simply wow.  Someone has a lot of hate.  I'm not even mocking you here, I am genually in awe of your dubious reasoning.<P>--------------------<P>C'mon Shammy Pants!
